# Database Schema & Data Patterns (v4)

## Core Tables

### journeys
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
user_id         UUID        REFERENCES auth.users(id) NOT NULL
title           TEXT        NOT NULL CHECK (char_length(title) <= 60)
why             TEXT        NOT NULL CHECK (char_length(why) <= 200)
category_id     UUID        REFERENCES journey_categories(id)
weekly_hours    NUMERIC     NOT NULL CHECK (weekly_hours >= 0.5 AND weekly_hours <= 20)
status          TEXT        NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' CHECK (status IN ('active', 'paused', 'archived'))
role            TEXT        NOT NULL DEFAULT 'primary' CHECK (role IN ('primary', 'secondary'))
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
paused_at       TIMESTAMPTZ
archived_at     TIMESTAMPTZ
```

### journey_categories
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
key             TEXT        NOT NULL UNIQUE
name            TEXT        NOT NULL
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
```

### actions
User-owned, reusable across journeys. Linked to journeys via journey_actions.
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
user_id         UUID        REFERENCES auth.users(id) NOT NULL
category_id     UUID        REFERENCES journey_categories(id)
title           TEXT        NOT NULL CHECK (char_length(title) <= 80)
is_active       BOOLEAN     NOT NULL DEFAULT true
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
```

### journey_actions
Junction: which actions are attached to which journey. Do not duplicate action rows; attach existing actions.
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
user_id         UUID        REFERENCES auth.users(id) NOT NULL
journey_id      UUID        REFERENCES journeys(id) NOT NULL
action_id       UUID        REFERENCES actions(id) NOT NULL
source          TEXT        NOT NULL CHECK (source IN ('suggested', 'custom'))
sort_order      INT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
UNIQUE(journey_id, action_id)
```

### action_logs
Multiple rows per day per journey allowed (one per action log entry). Zero-log day = no row for that journey/date.
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
user_id         UUID        REFERENCES auth.users(id) NOT NULL
journey_id      UUID        REFERENCES journeys(id) NOT NULL
action_id       UUID        REFERENCES actions(id) NOT NULL
log_date        DATE        NOT NULL
duration        NUMERIC     NOT NULL CHECK (duration IN (0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 3.0))
note            TEXT        CHECK (char_length(note) <= 140)
logged_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
```
Insert allowed only when the action is attached to the journey (journey_actions). Enforced by RLS and DB trigger.

### weekly_summaries
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
journey_id      UUID        REFERENCES journeys(id) NOT NULL
user_id         UUID        REFERENCES auth.users(id) NOT NULL
week_start      DATE        NOT NULL
commitment      NUMERIC     NOT NULL
actual          NUMERIC     NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
delta           NUMERIC     GENERATED ALWAYS AS (actual - commitment) STORED
zero_days       INTEGER     NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
needle_moved    BOOLEAN
recalibrated    BOOLEAN     DEFAULT false
skipped         BOOLEAN     DEFAULT false
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
UNIQUE(journey_id, week_start)
```
Compute actual and zero_days from action_logs: actual = SUM(duration) for journey/week; zero_days = days in week with no action_logs for that journey.

### recalibrations
```sql
id              UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
journey_id      UUID        REFERENCES journeys(id) NOT NULL
user_id         UUID        REFERENCES auth.users(id) NOT NULL
action          TEXT        NOT NULL CHECK (action IN ('reduce_target', 'reallocate', 'adjust_strategy', 'change_primary', 'pause'))
previous_value  TEXT
new_value       TEXT
reason          TEXT        CHECK (char_length(reason) <= 100)
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
```

## Constraints to Enforce in Application Logic
- Maximum 3 active journeys per user.
- Only 1 journey with role = 'primary' per user at any time.
- Paused journeys do not count toward the 3-journey cap.
- Weekly commitment changes take effect the following Monday.
- Actions are user-owned; reuse by attaching to journeys via journey_actions. Do not duplicate action records.
- action_logs: only insert when (journey_id, action_id) exists in journey_actions (enforced by RLS and trigger).

## Row Level Security
Every table must have RLS enabled with policies scoped to `auth.uid() = user_id` (or appropriate check). journey_categories: SELECT for authenticated users only. Never use service_role key on the client.

## Query Patterns
- Use `.select()` with explicit column lists — never `select('*')` in production.
- All inserts must include user_id from auth (e.g. auth.uid() or session.user.id in client).
- Weekly summaries: derive actual from SUM(action_logs.duration) grouped by journey_id and week; zero_days = count of week days with no action_logs for that journey.
- Filter by date ranges using `.gte()` and `.lte()` on date columns.
